menu "Mochi power management"

config MOCHI_DOZE_TIMEOUT_S
    int "Idle seconds before entering the Doze tier"
    default 60
    help
        Seconds with no touch/button before the device drops from Live to
        the Doze resting tier (WiFi power-save, stretched refresh, and —
        if MOCHI_LIGHT_SLEEP is set — automatic light sleep). 0 disables
        Doze entirely (always Live), which still records a clean Live
        power baseline through the power telemetry.

config MOCHI_DEEP_SLEEP_TIMEOUT_S
    int "Idle seconds in Doze before automatic deep sleep (0 = never)"
    default 0
    help
        Secondary timeout: continuous seconds spent dozing before the
        device commits to deep sleep to protect the battery. 0 leaves
        deep sleep as an explicit PWR-tap action only.

config MOCHI_DOZE_WIFI_POWERSAVE
    bool "Use WIFI_PS_MAX_MODEM while dozing"
    default y
    help
        Switch WiFi to maximum modem-sleep on Doze entry and back to
        min-modem (the IDF default) on wake. Safe and reversible; yields
        a real saving even without MOCHI_LIGHT_SLEEP.

config MOCHI_LIGHT_SLEEP
    bool "Enable automatic light sleep while dozing"
    default n
    select PM_ENABLE
    select FREERTOS_USE_TICKLESS_IDLE
    help
        While dozing, let the SoC enter automatic light sleep (esp_pm)
        between events. RAM and the e-paper image are retained; a touch
        (GPIO21 INT) or button wakes it in microseconds — unlike deep
        sleep, which reboots. Default OFF pending on-hardware validation
        (touch-INT wake on this board rev, WiFi/TLS coexistence, and the
        USB-Serial-JTAG console blocking light sleep on the bench). The
        power telemetry and tier accounting run regardless of this flag.

config MOCHI_PM_CPU_MAX_MHZ
    int "Max CPU frequency (MHz) under light sleep"
    depends on MOCHI_LIGHT_SLEEP
    default 240

config MOCHI_PM_CPU_MIN_MHZ
    int "Min CPU frequency (MHz) under light sleep"
    depends on MOCHI_LIGHT_SLEEP
    default 80

endmenu
